<br>
Active Member: One who attends most raids, Tries his best when he is there, and gives all that he can to make the guild better then the day before. These people are on just about every day, and normally, don't have lives (I'm guilty). These people put forth most of the effort in the guild to make it a better place to have fun while raiding big zones.<br>
<br>
Casual Members: People who normally are swamped by jobs and/or family life. They are on a few days a week, normally not during raid times or if so, not on very long during the raid. They are not required to come during FGR (Full Guild Raids) and are just in the guild to chat and have fun, rather then be a powergamer Active Member.<br>
<br>
MIA Members: These people are the &quot;Oh yeah, you played a few moths back, long time no see&quot; Or the people who have just disappeared.<br>
<br>
Phytir fell between the Casual and MIA. We actually would have had no idea where either Wilo or Phytir was if Wilo hadn't made a post on our boards saying they have spent the past few months playing NWN. <br>
<br>
I'm glad that you got me thinking of this because it brings a whole new angle to the whole problem. <br>
Phytir was a Casual Member. He was not an every day, lets kill @#%$ type of person. Giving him that weapon would have been like destroying it, because he would never been on to use it, thus giving that item to him would have been useless to begin with. As Kapen stated he had 17% attendance, which kinda tells you how much he played. Thats the thing I was trying to get to the whole time but I just never thought of it that way.<br>
<br>
And as to the 10 people camping, it should have been an obvious overstatement. There are probably three or four alts there I wouldn't doubt.<br>
<br>
I'm sure I speak for Tindi when I say that I'm sorry for what Zewt said. Having about 75% of this boards community being in smaller guilds probably insulted everyone of you. Ego is not a virtue, and I do not respect Zewt for what he said.<br>
<br>
I hope this has finally cleared the dust, and has now shown why we chose someone else, other then Phytir. I could have seen if it was a lesser item, but an item like the Willsaper is one desirable weapon and Key to MT strategy. <p><CENTER>
